vector is a container in c++ .
It is dynamic , that means that it grows (basically multiplies when the limit is reached like 2,4,8,16)
Syntax = #include<vector>
std::vector<int>hi;
std::vector<int> hi2 (5,12);//means create 5 boxes and fill 12 in them .
std::vector<int> hi3={1,2,3,4,5};
member function it supports are :- push_back(),pop_back(),emplace(),emplace_back(),resize(),swap(),erase(),clear().
